{
  "stem": "15768.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So it was a-- a very harrowing experience crossing the Atlantic.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I have, to this day, not been able really to ever think in terms of crossing the Atlantic on a ship again.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I-- I guess that's one of the things that has remained with me that-- that awful sensation and fear.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there we were in New York and found ourselves in the bosom of my mother's family.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We landed January 8, 1941, on my brother's birthday, which was another momentous occasion.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother's brother was at the pier to meet us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were to split up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was to live with an uncle who had two daughters, one older and one younger than myself by a year and a half.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my brother was going with a different uncle who had a young son.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it would be compatible for the two boys to sleep together and share a room.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my parents were going to take a furnished room.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they would have to immediately go to work, my mother doing housework, my father sweeping floors at Klein's department store.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember rather vividly my uncle heading home with me to-- to-- he lived out on the island in a small town.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when we came out of the subway at the Flushing station, there was a huge fruit and vegetable stand with great grapefruits and oranges and wonderful fruit.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I stood in front of it in-- in my weird clothing that said, you know, I'm from Europe, I'm from somewhere far away, and just wept and wept and cried and sobbed at the sight of all this wonderful food.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my uncle was so embarrassed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He walked a block away.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
